between the races.

75
00:04:33,567 --> 00:04:36,483
The leader of that group
was a wonderful man.

76
00:04:36,567 --> 00:04:40,067
He was the lord of
the domain of Seyaette.

77
00:04:40,150 --> 00:04:42,275
But after he died
in the first Wave,

78
00:04:42,358 --> 00:04:44,233
all the nobles who
had sided with him

79
00:04:44,317 --> 00:04:46,317
were banished
under Father's orders

80
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:49,858
to the most remote
regions of the kingdom.

81
00:04:49,942 --> 00:04:53,108
What is the king's
problem with demi-humans?

82
00:04:53,192 --> 00:04:54,483
Huh?

83
00:04:54,567 --> 00:04:57,733
Raphtalia? What's wrong?

84
00:04:57,817 --> 00:05:02,567
The village my family's from.
It was in the Seyaette district.

85
00:05:02,650 --> 00:05:04,317
I heard that
after the first Wave

86
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:07,317
the Seyaette region
was badly hit by rioters.

87
00:05:08,483 --> 00:05:10,567
I'm afraid it was.

88
00:05:14,358 --> 00:05:15,358
[RAPHTALIA]
My village was attacked

89
00:05:15,442 --> 00:05:17,067
by a mob of
Melromarc's soldiers

90
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:19,942
who were totally
out of control.

91
00:05:20,025 --> 00:05:21,650
The more I hear
about these scum,

92
00:05:21,733 --> 00:05:23,775
the more I'm disgusted.

93
00:05:26,108 --> 00:05:27,692
[MELTY]
I'm so sorry.

94
00:05:27,775 --> 00:05:30,567
But, Melty, it's not
like it was your fault.

95
00:05:30,650 --> 00:05:32,817
[MELTY] As royalty,
there must have been something

96
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:34,650
we could have done.

97
00:05:34,733 --> 00:05:37,192
But we did nothing to help.

98
00:05:37,275 --> 00:05:39,358
Raphtalia, tell me
everything you remember

99
00:05:39,442 --> 00:05:41,067
about those soldiers.

100
00:05:41,150 --> 00:05:41,983
Huh?

101
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:43,275
Once things have
been cleared up,

102
00:05:43,358 --> 00:05:46,525
I'll make sure they're
brought to justice.

103
00:05:48,025 --> 00:05:49,525
Thank you.

104
00:05:49,608 --> 00:05:53,775
Okay, so this nobleman that you
know lives around here, right?

105
00:05:53,858 --> 00:05:54,900
[MELTY]
Yes.

106
00:05:54,983 --> 00:05:56,525
The real question
is whether or not

107
00:05:56,608 --> 00:05:58,733
we can actually trust this guy.

108
00:05:58,817 --> 00:06:00,983
[VAN]
You are indeed correct.

109
00:06:01,067 --> 00:06:02,233
[RAPHTALIA, FILO, MELTY]
Huh?

110
00:06:10,275 --> 00:06:12,817
It's been too long,
hasn't it, Reichnott?

111
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:16,317
Princess Melty,
it's so good to see you again.

112
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:18,275
Very pleased to meet you.

113
00:06:18,358 --> 00:06:20,275
You may call me Van Reichnott.

114
00:06:20,358 --> 00:06:22,942
I am the reigning lord
of this region.

115
00:06:23,025 --> 00:06:26,442
[NAOFUMI] Wait, this wimp is the
nobleman she was talking about?

116
00:06:26,525 --> 00:06:28,233
But his stealth
is off the charts.

117
00:06:28,317 --> 00:06:30,692
How the hell did he do that?

118
00:06:30,775 --> 00:06:32,942
However, this is
no place for a chat.

119
00:06:33,025 --> 00:06:35,650
Why don't you come over
to the house and we'll talk?

120
00:06:38,983 --> 00:06:40,525
[VAN]
I see.

121
00:06:40,608 --> 00:06:44,525
So you reached my domain after
escaping Melromarc's forces,

122
00:06:44,608 --> 00:06:45,942
is that it?

123
00:06:46,025 --> 00:06:47,358
[NAOFUMI]
Yeah.

124
00:06:47,442 --> 00:06:49,317
The knights have informed
me that you were the one

125
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:50,858
who started the
wildfires in order

126
00:06:50,942 --> 00:06:52,608
to cover your tracks,
Sir Shield Hero.

127
00:06:52,692 --> 00:06:54,858
Would you consider that
account to be accurate?

128
00:06:54,942 --> 00:06:56,733
That's a complete lie.

129
00:06:56,817 --> 00:06:59,900
I can guarantee the other
princess is behind that.

130
00:06:59,983 --> 00:07:01,192
[VAN]
I thought so.

131
00:07:01,275 --> 00:07:03,483
In fact, when I ran into
your party in the woods,

132
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:05,692
I had been patrolling
the area out of concern

133
00:07:05,775 --> 00:07:07,608
for Princess Melty.

134
00:07:07,692 --> 00:07:09,900
You must be exhausted
from your travels.

135
00:07:09,983 --> 00:07:12,233
You're more than welcome
to rest up here for a while,

136
00:07:12,317 --> 00:07:13,317
if you wish.

137
00:07:15,233 --> 00:07:17,692
[FILO]
Ooh! Wow!

138
00:07:17,775 --> 00:07:20,192
May I eat now, Master?
Please, can I eat?

139
00:07:20,275 --> 00:07:21,067
[NAOFUMI]
No, wait.

140
00:07:21,150 --> 00:07:22,317
Huh?

141
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:25,400
Not till I'm convinced
we can trust this guy.

142
00:07:25,483 --> 00:07:26,692
[VAN]
Mmm!

143
00:07:26,775 --> 00:07:29,442
Absolutely exquisite!

144
00:07:29,525 --> 00:07:32,942
Rest assured,
the food isn't poisoned.

145
00:07:33,025 --> 00:07:35,317
Okay, everybody, time to eat!

146
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:36,400
[RAPHTALIA]
Filo!

147
00:07:36,483 --> 00:07:38,858
Where're your manners?
Put that down!

148
00:07:38,942 --> 00:07:40,483
'Kay...

149
00:07:43,150 --> 00:07:45,942
Come on, Master Naofumi,
I'm sure it's safe to eat.

150
00:07:46,025 --> 00:07:48,317
It's incredibly
rude to cast such doubts

151
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:50,567
on his gracious hospitality.

152
00:07:50,650 --> 00:07:53,067
We're not gonna
be here that long.

153
00:07:53,150 --> 00:07:56,650
We're leaving tomorrow
morning at dawn.

154
00:07:56,733 --> 00:07:58,025
But why so soon?

155
00:07:58,108 --> 00:08:00,192
[NAOFUMI]
The longer we stay,

156
00:08:00,275 --> 00:08:02,775
the higher the odds of us
being sniffed out.

157
00:08:02,858 --> 00:08:04,775
Well, yes, but I was, ehm...

158
00:08:04,858 --> 00:08:07,608
I was hoping to be able
to rest a little more.

159
00:08:07,692 --> 00:08:09,900
Princess Melty, if you'll
allow me to say so,

160
00:08:09,983 --> 00:08:10,900
it appears you've grown.

161
00:08:10,983 --> 00:08:12,150
[MELTY]
Huh?

162
00:08:12,233 --> 00:08:14,567
In the past, you used to
affect a mature attitude

163
00:08:14,650 --> 00:08:16,525
that went beyond your years...

164
00:08:16,608 --> 00:08:18,817
However, since you've been
traveling with the Shield Hero,

165
00:08:18,900 --> 00:08:23,567
I'd say it's helped you to grow,
and I mean that in a good way.

166
00:08:23,650 --> 00:08:25,400
[NAOFUMI] I'm pretty sure
you mean it in a bad way.

167
00:08:25,483 --> 00:08:27,275
What?! You keep quiet, you--!

168
00:08:27,358 --> 00:08:28,483
[NAOFUMI]
Quit making such a racket,

169
00:08:28,567 --> 00:08:29,692
we're trying to eat here.

170
00:08:29,775 --> 00:08:31,483
[MELTY] Whose fault
do you think that is?!

171
00:08:31,567 --> 00:08:33,067
[RAPHTALIA sighs]

172
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:34,483
Oh, wow!

173
00:08:34,567 --> 00:08:36,900
This feels amazing!

174
00:08:36,983 --> 00:08:39,775
So soft and bouncy!

175
00:08:41,025 --> 00:08:43,650
You need to get some rest.
Why don't you sleep?

176
00:08:43,733 --> 00:08:44,733
There's no way of knowing

177
00:08:44,817 --> 00:08:46,942
when this place is
gonna be attacked.

178
00:08:47,025 --> 00:08:50,650
I make it a point of not
sleeping at times like these.

179
00:08:50,733 --> 00:08:53,108
Master Naofumi,
why don't I keep watch,

180
00:08:53,192 --> 00:08:56,567
that way you can go ahead
and get some sleep?

181
00:08:56,650 --> 00:08:58,525
All right.

182
00:08:58,608 --> 00:09:00,025
[MELTY]
Wait a minute.

183
00:09:00,108 --> 00:09:02,900
Why do you listen to what
Raphtalia says, but not to me?

184
00:09:02,983 --> 00:09:04,525
[NAOFUMI]
Don't worry about it.

185
00:09:06,817 --> 00:09:08,108
Hey, I know.

186
00:09:08,192 --> 00:09:11,650
You and I can do some
exploring around this place.

187
00:09:11,733 --> 00:09:13,692
Sure. Let's go.

188
00:09:15,817 --> 00:09:18,983
[FILO] I wonder if they have
some yummy snacks anywhere...

189
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:23,400
Would it hurt if you
were a bit nicer to her?

190
00:09:23,483 --> 00:09:26,108
It wouldn't cost
you anything, y'know.

191
00:09:30,817 --> 00:09:32,025
Huh?

192
00:09:34,025 --> 00:09:35,817
[FILO]
What's wrong, Mel?

193
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:37,942
I don't understand why,
but I think I've been acting

194
00:09:38,025 --> 00:09:40,733
really spoiled since
meeting Naofumi.

195
00:09:40,817 --> 00:09:43,942
Even my speech has
become more crude as well.

196
00:09:44,025 --> 00:09:47,733
I feel like a different person,
and I'm not sure I like her.

197
00:09:47,817 --> 00:09:49,483
Well, I, umm...

198
00:09:49,567 --> 00:09:52,817
I'm sorry. You don't really
understand me, do you?

199
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:55,275
Well, not exactly,
but I still love you!

200
00:09:55,358 --> 00:09:56,608
Huh?

201
00:09:56,692 --> 00:09:58,650
I mean, you always look
so cheerful and everything

202
00:09:58,733 --> 00:10:01,608
when you're talking to Master,
so I can tell you like him.

203
00:10:01,692 --> 00:10:03,108
Oh, really?

204
00:10:03,192 --> 00:10:05,400
I know, all you have to
do is get him to dote on you

205
00:10:05,483 --> 00:10:07,775
just like he does us.
it's simple!

206
00:10:07,858 --> 00:10:10,150
What...?! Wait, no!

207
00:10:10,233 --> 00:10:11,233
[FILO]
Yep!

208
00:10:11,317 --> 00:10:12,733
But that isn't...
I mean, I don't...

209
00:10:12,817 --> 00:10:15,108
That's not really what
I'm looking for from him!

210
00:10:19,108 --> 00:10:21,442
[AULTCRAY]
You still haven't found her?!

211
00:10:21,525 --> 00:10:22,942
If anything happens to Melty,

212
00:10:23,025 --> 00:10:25,733
I'll have every one of your
miserable heads on a pike!

213
00:10:25,817 --> 00:10:27,483
[KNIGHTS]
Yes, sire!

214
00:10:30,275 --> 00:10:31,733
Rest assured, Father.

215
00:10:31,817 --> 00:10:35,858
I promise you I will find Melty
and bring her back home to us.

216
00:10:35,942 --> 00:10:37,733
Do what you can.

217
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:44,525
This can't happen
to my family again.

218
00:10:44,608 --> 00:10:48,317
How much do you intend
to make me suffer?

219
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:50,358
Accursed Shield!

220
00:10:51,608 --> 00:10:52,942
[MELTY]
You're up?

221
00:10:53,025 --> 00:10:53,900
[NAOFUMI]
Yeah.

222
00:10:53,983 --> 00:10:55,483
I'll take over now.

223
00:10:55,567 --> 00:10:56,733
[MELTY]
It's fine.

224
00:10:56,817 --> 00:10:59,317
I'm really not
very sleepy, actually.

225
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,942
What's the matter?

226
00:11:01,025 --> 00:11:02,650
[MELTY]
Naofumi, I...

227
00:11:02,733 --> 00:11:03,942
What is it?

228
00:11:04,025 --> 00:11:05,775
I was just thinking that,
as a crown princess,

229
00:11:05,858 --> 00:11:08,608
should I really
keep running like this?

230
00:11:08,692 --> 00:11:10,067
As a member of the royal family,

231
00:11:10,150 --> 00:11:12,733
there's just so much
more I could be doing.

232
00:11:12,817 --> 00:11:16,775
But I find I'm doing nothing
because I keep running.

233
00:11:16,858 --> 00:11:19,817
[NAOFUMI] You know, your life
comes before anything else.

234
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:22,483
So you can worry about
your duties once you're safe

235
00:11:22,567 --> 00:11:23,817
and out of danger.

236
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:26,858
[MELTY]
But I feel so pathetic.

237
00:11:29,817 --> 00:11:33,775
Don't be so hard on yourself.
Get some rest now.

238
00:11:33,858 --> 00:11:35,150
[MELTY]
Okay.

239
00:11:36,192 --> 00:11:37,608
Don't worry.

240
00:11:37,692 --> 00:11:40,442
I'm sure there are things that
only you can take care of.

241
00:11:41,942 --> 00:11:43,358
[MELTY]
Thanks. Umm...

242
00:11:43,442 --> 00:11:44,192
[NAOFUMI]
Hm?

243
00:11:44,275 --> 00:11:45,233
It's nothing.

244
00:11:45,317 --> 00:11:46,650
